   Meet Frederick E. (Fritz) Hitchcock, President


   Frederick E. (Fritz) Hitchcock

   Frederick E. (Fritz) Hitchcock, Dealer Member, has served on the Board
   since December 1997. Mr. Hitchcock is Vice President of the Board, a
   member of the Executive Committee and served previously as Chair of the
   Education Committee, and as a member of the Corrective Action Plan
   Committee. An Iowa native, Mr. Hitchcock began his automotive career in
   1961 with Chrysler's Dodge Division. Mr. Hitchcock is Chairman and CEO
   of Hitchcock Automotive Resources, which was ranked the 32nd largest
   privately-held company in Los Angeles County for 2000 by Los Angeles
   Business Journal, and the 39th largest U.S. dealer group for 1999 by
   Automotive News. Currently, Mr. Hitchcock owns and operates Puente
   Hills Toyota, Puente Hills Ford, Puente Hills Volkswagen, Northridge
   Toyota, Fullerton Toyota, and South Bay BMW. Collectively, Mr.
   Hitchcock's dealerships employ over 700 employees. Mr. Hitchcock has
   served as Chairman of the American International Automobile Dealers
   Association and President of the California Motor Car Dealers
   Association. Mr. Hitchcock was appointed to the National Highway Safety
   Advisory Board by President Ronald Reagan and to the President's
   Commission on White House Fellowship by President George Bush. In 1995
   and 1998, Mr. Hitchcock received the All-star Dealer Award from Sports
   Illustrated and in 1993 received the Quality Dealer Award from Time
   magazine. Appointed to the Board by former Governor Pete Wilson, Mr.
   Hitchcock's current term will expire on January 15, 2002.

